\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{2e}<\int_0^{+\infty}e^{-x^2}dx<1+\frac{1}{2e}
u=-x^2
\int_0^{\infty}e^{-x^2}dx =\int_{0}^{1}e^{-x^2}dx+\int_{1}^{\infty} e^{-x^2} dx <\int_{0}^{1}1 dx+\int_{1}^{\infty} x e^{-x^2} dx  =1+\frac{1}{2e}
u=-x^2
\int_0^{\infty}e^{-x^2}dx > \int_{0}^{1}e^{-x^2}dx > \int_{0}^{1} xe^{-x^2} dx =\frac{1}{2}-\frac{1}{2e}
